    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The action of joining two discontinuous lengths of material together into one, as in weaving together two ends of rope, making a joint in magnetic tape or film, or lapping two pieces of timber into a continuous length.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000008771/Roberts, Construction Industry Thesaurus (1976)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>De handeling van het samenvoegen van twee onderbroken stukken materiaal tot één, zoals het aan elkaar wevenvan twee uiteinden van touw, het maken van een verbinding in magnetische tape of film, of het omwikkelen van twee stukken hout in een ononderbroken lengte.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052381/Van Dale Engels-Nederlands (1989)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>將兩段不連續長度的材料接合唯一的行為，例如將繩索的兩端編織在一起、於磁帶或底片上製作接頭或將兩塊木材搭接為連續的一段長度。
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
